cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for evaluating distributed representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves evaluating state-of-the-art embeddings, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of clustering algorithms and outlier detection techniques suggests the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves creating a gold-standard dataset, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
